==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Particularism
<hw>Par*tic"u*lar*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>particularisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A minute description;
a detailed statement.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine of particular
election.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(German Politics)</fld> <def>Devotion to the
interests of one's own kingdom or province rather than to those of the
empire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Particularist</ent>⟦br⟧
